Tony,

I know this would be one hell of a feat---just grabbing the glued on
veneer---

The glues that are used to stick this stuff on the composition board, is
almost bullet proof, and would be tough to lift just the veneer without
splitting or damaging it---

I think almost impossible--unless you had a band saw with a large enough
throat to accept the door's---but even then, you'd need a huge fence,
darn near on both sides, to get a straight cut just below the veneer---

Almost not doable

My thoughts on this one--

Later,

Terry

 
